lved transactions with banks such as barclays plc and deutsche bank ag — through which profits converted from rapid trading were converted into lowertaxed longterm capital gains the strategy was also questioned by the internal revenue service irs the higher rates for the five years under investigation would have been  percent to  whereas the lower rate was from  percent to  percent the irs contended that the arrangement renaissance’s medallion fund had with the banks in which the fund owned option contracts rather than the underlying financial instruments is a ruse and that the fund investors owe taxes at the higher rate because medallion could claim that it owned just one asset – the option – and held it for more than a year investors could declare their gains to be longterm investments — bloomberg  campaign contributionsedit according to the center for responsive politics renaissance is the top financial firm contributing to federal campaigns in the  election cycle donating  by july by comparison over that same period sixth ranked soros fund management has contributed  renaissances managers have also been active in the  cycle contributing nearly  million by june with mercer ranking as the  individual federal donor largely to republicans and simons ranked  largely to democrats during the  campaign cycle simons contributed  ranking as the th largest individual contributor simons directed all but  of his funds towards liberal candidates mercer contributed  ranking as the th largest individual contributor mercer directed all funds contributed towards conservative candidates since  renaissance has contributed  to federal campaigns and since  has spent  on lobbying see alsoedit d e shaw  co pdt partners two sigma investments referencesedit  a b patterson scott  march  pioneering fund stages second act wall street journal retrieved  november    renaissance technologies llc brightscope retrieved  november    a b renaissance technologies credio retrieved  november    a b c